@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>Last Updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>

<h3>1. Introduction</h3>
<p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how E-Library collects, uses, and protects your information.</p>

<h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Personal details (e.g., name, email) when you register.</li>
    <li>Browsing and usage data (e.g., books viewed, searches).</li>
    <li>Communication data (e.g., messages, support requests).</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. How We Use Your Information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To provide and personalize your library experience.</li>
    <li>To improve our services and security.</li>
    <li>To send important updates or promotional content (optional).</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Data Protection</h3>
<p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>

<h3>5. Cookies & Tracking</h3>
<p>We may use cookies to enhance user experience. You can disable cookies in your browser settings.</p>

<h3>6. Third-Party Services</h3>
<p>We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties, except as required by law.</p>

<h3>7. Your Rights</h3>
<p>You can request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data by contacting us.</p>

<h3>8. Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions about this policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@elibrary.com">support@elibrary.com</a>.</p>
